The server rules generally match the Discord guidelines by a principle: &ldquo;the severity of a violation together with social behavior leads to appropriate punishment within the community&rdquo;
The rules are short and subjective in social conflicts. Moderators keep order without inflated rights, although auto-moderation bot is enough in many cases. Just in case, contact with: ZwerOxotnik#7117
However, we cannot use &ldquo;A Code of Conduct&rdquo; to the full (For instance &ldquo;Contributor Covenant&rdquo; because of different goals of groups of people.
